Source: twom
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Bron Gondwana <brong@fastmailteam.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), uuid-dev, pkg-config
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/brong/twom
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: libtwom0
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: skiplist key-value store with MVCC - shared library
 twom is a file-backed ordered key-value database providing sorted key
 iteration, transactions with commit/abort, MVCC for serializable
 isolation, cursors, binary keys and values, checksummed records,
 crash recovery, and compaction.
 .
 This package contains the shared library.

Package: libtwom-dev
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Section: libdevel
Depends: libtwom0 (= ${binary:Version}), uuid-dev, ${misc:Depends}
Description: skiplist key-value store with MVCC - development files
 twom is a file-backed ordered key-value database providing sorted key
 iteration, transactions with commit/abort, MVCC for serializable
 isolation, cursors, binary keys and values, checksummed records,
 crash recovery, and compaction.
 .
 This package contains the static library, header file, and
 pkg-config file needed for development.

Package: twom-tools
Architecture: any
Section: utils
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: skiplist key-value store with MVCC - command-line tools
 twom is a file-backed ordered key-value database providing sorted key
 iteration, transactions with commit/abort, MVCC for serializable
 isolation, cursors, binary keys and values, checksummed records,
 crash recovery, and compaction.
 .
 This package contains twomtool, a command-line utility for
 inspecting and manipulating twom databases.
